-- Japan's Crude Steel Output May Decline 1.5% Next Quarter, Ministry Says
-- B y   M a s u m i   S u g a
-- 2010-09-29T04:39:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/japan-s-crude-steel-output-may-decline-1-5-next-quarter-ministry-says.html
Steel output in Japan, the second-
biggest producer, will likely fall 1.5 percent in the quarter
starting Oct. 1 from the current quarter, the trade ministry
said.  Crude steel production will likely decline to 26.98 million
metric tons next quarter from 27.38 million tons in the current
three months, the Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry said
today in a  statement .  To contact the reporters on this story:
 Masumi Suga  in Tokyo at 
